22/06/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The police chief of Republika Srpska (RS) said on Monday (21 June) that Radovan Karadzic and his wartime commander Ratko Mladic have left the country. Radomir Njegus insisted that the world's two most wanted war crime suspects have not visited the Bosnian Serb entity for a long time. He added, however, that his service is trying to locate 16 other indictees and may arrest some of them before the NATO summit in Istanbul later this month.
In other news, RS Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic met with his Serbian counterpart, Vojislav Kostunica, in Belgrade on Monday. They discussed issues related NATO's Partnership for Peace programme and agreed on further steps are needed to enhance bilateral and regional co-operation. (Reuters, AFP, Pincom.info, Fena, PBS BiH, RS government Web site, Srna - 21/06/04)
